{"id":"5e9c31629b6559241525dd10","artists":["5e9b695d7a1236eccfeb26be"],"title":"New: Various Cruelties – ‘Neon Truth/She Is The One’","content":"<p><a rel=\"attachment wp-att-6150\" href=\"https://admin.</p><p>crackintheroad.com/music/6137-new-various-cruelties-neon-truthshe-is-the-one/attachment/various\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-6150\" title=\"various\" src=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/uploads/2011/03/various.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"444\" srcset=\"https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/03/various.jpg 780w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/03/various-260x148.jpg 260w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/03/various-640x364.jpg 640w, https://api.crackintheroad.com/images/2011/03/various-165x93.jpg 165w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" /></a></p>\n<p>After <strong>Crack In The Road </strong>were the first blog to feature <strong>Various Cruelties</strong> (can you tell I’m proud of that?), the band have gone on to receive a great deal of attention from fans and critics alike, not to mention a fair amount of national radio play. After successfully releasing their debut single ‘<strong>If It Wasn’t For You</strong>‘ towards the end of last year, the band return with their sophomore effort ‘<strong>Neon Truth</strong>‘ and ‘<strong>She Is The One</strong>‘. A fantastic development in their sound, ‘<strong>Neon Truth</strong>‘ is an upbeat affair with jangly guitars and soaring vocals, whereas ‘<strong>She Is The One</strong>‘ is a much slower, and more soulful experience. A very promising release by a very promising band, and you will be able to buy the single from the <strong>23rd May</strong>.</p>\n<p><object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" width=\"100%\" height=\"81\" codebase=\"https://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\"><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><param name=\"src\" value=\"https://player.soundcloud.com/pl